# Invitation (A6 print-ready) rules

- Keep `invitation/` output **print-ready A6**: \(105mm × 148mm\).
- Use **mm units** for layout/typography where possible; avoid px-only sizing for print.
- Invitation template structure (keep these sections present in `invitation/index.html`):
  - Top invocation text: **"om Pachai amman thunai"**
  - A **title** (editable)
  - A main image using a local house asset (prefer `invitation/house3d.svg` for crisp print; `invitation/house.png` is acceptable)
  - **Date and time** of the event (editable)
- Ensure print correctness:
  - `@page { size: 105mm 148mm; margin: 0; }`
  - The card container must be exactly `width: 105mm; height: 148mm;`
  - Use `print-color-adjust: exact` (and `-webkit-print-color-adjust`) when using backgrounds.
- Screen vs print:
  - Screen can have 3D/hover effects, deep shadows, and perspective.
  - Print must be **flat and clean** (no reliance on hover/animation to look good).
- Avoid external network dependencies (CDN fonts/images). If needed, prefer local assets under `invitation/assets/`.

